## Session Search + Filter Plan v3 — Addressing Stress Findings F1-F4

### Revision Notes

This v3 revision addresses 4 findings from stress testing of the v2 execution:

| Finding | Severity | Root Cause | Fix |
|---|---|---|---|
| **F1** | BLOCKER | uniqueAgents/uniqueModels computed from records() which includes .slice(0, HOME_SESSION_LIMIT=15). Agents/models beyond 15th session invisible in dropdown. | Split records() into fullRecords (pre-slice) + records (sliced). Derive filter options from fullRecords. |
| **F2** | MAJOR | onClear() calls setState('search', '') but doesn't call debouncedSetSearch.clear(). User can type, clear within 200ms, stale debounce fires re-applying old query. | Add debouncedSetSearch.clear() before setState in onClear handler. |
| **F3** | MAJOR | declare module augmentation for Session type with agent/model fields was not added to executed code. If SDK types are stale, TS compilation fails on session.agent / session.model?.id. | Add declare module "@opencode-ai/sdk/v2/client" augmentation after imports in home.tsx. |
| **F4** | MAJOR | Self-referential filter dropdowns — filter options computed from already-filtered records (same root cause as F1). Users can't discover agents/models beyond first 15 sessions. | Combined fix with F1: fullRecords() provides the full pool. |

### Current Execution State (v2 progress)

The following v2 fixes are ALREADY in the dirty working tree and verified:

- ✅ **Fix B (debounce)**: `debouncedSetSearch` created via `debounce()` from `@solid-primitives/scheduled`, `onCleanup` registered
- ✅ **Fix C (fuzzysort)**: `fuzzysort.single()` used in filter pipeline; `session.summary` (stats object) NOT included
- ✅ **Fix D (agent filter)**: `state.agentFilter` in store, `record.session.agent` comparison in filter pipeline, RadioGroup UI
- ✅ **Fix E (model filter)**: `state.modelFilter` in store, `record.session.model?.id` comparison, RadioGroup UI
- ✅ **Fix F (i18n keys)**: All 9 `home.sessions.filter.*` keys exist in both `en.ts` and `zh.ts`

The following v2 fixes are NOT yet applied and are still needed:

- ❌ **Fix SDK (type augmentation)**: `declare module "@opencode-ai/sdk/v2/client"` block absent from executed code

### New Fix G — Split records() into fullRecords + records (F1+F4)

**Root Cause**: The `records` memo applies `.slice(0, HOME_SESSION_LIMIT)` at the end of its pipeline. Both `uniqueAgents` and `uniqueModels` iterate over `records()`, so they only see at most 15 sessions' worth of agents and models. Sessions 16+ are invisible in filter dropdowns.

**Surgical Fix**: Extract the pre-slice computation into a new `fullRecords` memo. Keep `records` as a lightweight `.slice()` wrapper. Change `uniqueAgents`/`uniqueModels` to iterate over `fullRecords()`.

**File**: `packages/app/src/pages/home.tsx`

**Before** (in HomeDesign, current records creation):
```ts
  const records = createMemo(() => {
    return [
      ...new Map(
        projectDirectories()
          .flatMap((directory) => sortedRootSessions(sync.child(directory, { bootstrap: false })[0], Date.now()))
          .map((session) => [`${pathKey(session.directory)}:${session.id}`, session] as const),
      ).values(),
    ]
      .sort((a, b) => (b.time.updated ?? b.time.created) - (a.time.updated ?? a.time.created))
      .flatMap((session) => {
        const project = projectForSession(session, projects(), projectByID())
        if (!project) return []
        return { session, project, projectName: displayName(project) }
      })
      .filter((record) => {
        const value = search()
        if (value && !fuzzysort.single(value, `${record.session.title ?? ""} ${record.projectName}`)) return false
        if (state.timeFilter !== "all") { /* time filter logic */ }
        if (state.agentFilter && record.session.agent !== state.agentFilter) return false
        if (state.modelFilter && record.session.model?.id !== state.modelFilter) return false
        return true
      })
      .slice(0, HOME_SESSION_LIMIT)  // ← truncates to 15
  })
  const groups = createMemo(() => groupSessions(records(), language))
  const uniqueAgents = createMemo(() => {
    const agents = new Set<string>()
    for (const record of records()) {      // ← only 15 records
      if (record.session.agent) agents.add(record.session.agent)
    }
    return [...agents].sort()
  })
  const uniqueModels = createMemo(() => {
    const models = new Set<string>()
    for (const record of records()) {      // ← only 15 records
      if (record.session.model?.id) models.add(record.session.model.id)
    }
    return [...models].sort()
  })
```

**After**:
```ts
  const fullRecords = createMemo(() => {
    return [
      ...new Map(
        projectDirectories()
          .flatMap((directory) => sortedRootSessions(sync.child(directory, { bootstrap: false })[0], Date.now()))
          .map((session) => [`${pathKey(session.directory)}:${session.id}`, session] as const),
      ).values(),
    ]
      .sort((a, b) => (b.time.updated ?? b.time.created) - (a.time.updated ?? a.time.created))
      .flatMap((session) => {
        const project = projectForSession(session, projects(), projectByID())
        if (!project) return []
        return { session, project, projectName: displayName(project) }
      })
      .filter((record) => {
        const value = search()
        if (value && !fuzzysort.single(value, `${record.session.title ?? ""} ${record.projectName}`)) return false
        if (state.timeFilter !== "all") { /* time filter logic */ }
        if (state.agentFilter && record.session.agent !== state.agentFilter) return false
        if (state.modelFilter && record.session.model?.id !== state.modelFilter) return false
        return true
      })
      // ← NO .slice() here
  })
  const records = createMemo(() => fullRecords().slice(0, HOME_SESSION_LIMIT))
  const groups = createMemo(() => groupSessions(records(), language))
  const uniqueAgents = createMemo(() => {
    const agents = new Set<string>()
    for (const record of fullRecords()) {   // ← all matching sessions
      if (record.session.agent) agents.add(record.session.agent)
    }
    return [...agents].sort()
  })
  const uniqueModels = createMemo(() => {
    const models = new Set<string>()
    for (const record of fullRecords()) {   // ← all matching sessions
      if (record.session.model?.id) models.add(record.session.model.id)
    }
    return [...models].sort()
  })
```

**Lines changed**: ~8 (rename `records` → `fullRecords`, strip `.slice()`, add new `records` memo, change iteration target in uniqueAgents/uniqueModels).

**Internal note for executor**: The `records` variable declaration must change from `const records = createMemo(() => { ... .slice(0, HOME_SESSION_LIMIT) })` to `const fullRecords = createMemo(() => { ... })` (remove .slice), then add `const records = createMemo(() => fullRecords().slice(0, HOME_SESSION_LIMIT))` immediately after, then change the two `for (const record of records())` in `uniqueAgents`/`uniqueModels` to `for (const record of fullRecords())`.

**Impact**: Filter dropdowns fully discoverable. Agent/Model options from ALL sessions (within current active filters) are shown, not just the first 15.

**Risk**: `fullRecords` may contain hundreds of records if no filter is active. The Set deduplication means O(n) scan which is fine — Solid's memoization only re-executes when inputs change. No performance concern since `sortedRootSessions` already creates the full list server-side.

### New Fix H — Debounce clear race condition (F2)

**Root Cause**: When the user clicks the clear button, `onClear` calls `setState("search", "")` but does not cancel the pending debounce timer. If the user typed something, then clicked clear within 200ms, the debounce timer fires after the clear, re-applying the previous query string.

**Surgical Fix**: Call `debouncedSetSearch.clear()` before `setState` in the `onClear` handler.

**File**: `packages/app/src/pages/home.tsx`

**Before** (in HomeDesign return JSX, HomeSessionSearch onClear prop):
```tsx
            onClear={() => setState("search", "")}
```

**After**:
```tsx
            onClear={() => { debouncedSetSearch.clear(); setState("search", ""); }}
```

**Lines changed**: 1.

**Impact**: Stale debounce timer never fires after clear. Race condition eliminated.

**Risk**: None — `debouncedSetSearch` is already imported and initialized in scope. `clear()` is a standard method on the debounce primitive.

### Confirm Fix I — Type augmentation (F3)

**Root Cause**: The `declare module "@opencode-ai/sdk/v2/client"` augmentation was planned in v2 (Fix SDK) but was not added to the executed code. If the generated SDK types are stale, TS compilation fails on `session.agent` and `session.model` access.

**Surgical Fix**: Add the augmentation block after the import statements, before any code.

**File**: `packages/app/src/pages/home.tsx`

**Before** (line 36 is the last import, line 38 is `const HOME_SESSION_LIMIT`):
```ts
import { useSettings } from "@/context/settings"

const HOME_SESSION_LIMIT = 15
```

**After** (insert between imports and constant definitions):
```ts
import { useSettings } from "@/context/settings"

// Local type augmentation: v2 generated Session type includes agent and model
// but stale builds may miss them. Augment here for safety.
declare module "@opencode-ai/sdk/v2/client" {
  interface Session {
    agent?: string
    model?: {
      id: string
      providerID: string
      variant?: string
    }
  }
}

const HOME_SESSION_LIMIT = 15
```

**Lines changed**: +7 (comments + declaration).

**Impact**: Interface declaration merging is additive. If v2 types already expose `agent` and `model`, the augmentation merges harmlessly. Zero runtime cost.

**Risk**: None. If SDK types are regenerated correctly, this augmentation becomes a no-op.

### Changed Files Summary

| File | Change | Lines |
|---|---|---|
| `packages/app/src/pages/home.tsx` | Fix G: split records into fullRecords+records, filter options from fullRecords | ~8 changed |
| `packages/app/src/pages/home.tsx` | Fix H: add debouncedSetSearch.clear() in onClear | 1 changed |
| `packages/app/src/pages/home.tsx` | Fix I: add declare module type augmentation | +7 |

No i18n files changed — all keys already exist.

### Apply Order

1. **Fix I** (type augmentation) — must exist before TS compilation references agent/model on Session
2. **Fix G** (fullRecords split) — changes records memo + uniqueAgents/uniqueModels
3. **Fix H** (debounce clear) — single-line change in JSX, independent

### Rollback Plan

Revert in reverse order: H → G → I. Each fix is a clean independent commit.

### Validation

```bash
cd packages/app && bun typecheck
cd packages/app && bun test --filter "home"  # if home tests exist
```

**Manual verification checklist:**
1. Filter dropdown shows agents from ALL sessions, not just the first 15
2. Filter dropdown shows models from ALL sessions, not just the first 15
3. Click clear button with a pending debounce — search does NOT reapply stale query
4. TypeScript compiles without errors on `session.agent`, `session.model?.id`
5. All prior v2 behaviors preserved: fuzzy search, time filter, agent filter, model filter, i18n labels

### Pre-existing Dirty Files

- `packages/app/src/pages/home.tsx` — Already dirty with v2 changes. Fixes G, H, I are additive.

### Edge Cases & Risks

| Risk | Mitigation |
|---|---|
| `fullRecords()` returns thousands of sessions | Solid's `createMemo` caches until inputs change. Unique-agent scan is O(n) per render — acceptable for desktop app. |
| `debouncedSetSearch` not in scope at JSX `onClear` site | Already defined at function scope in HomeDesign, before the return statement. Verified by current executed code. |
| Type augmentation conflicts with future SDK rebuild | Interface merging is additive. Same-shape declarations merge cleanly. Can be removed when SDK rebuild is standardized. |
